<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="375" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="18.[140,1107,588,756]" pageId="18" pageNumber="375">
This Holarctic species is newly recorded in 
<collectingRegion box="[688,827,659,686]" country="Canada" name="Nova Scotia" pageId="18" pageNumber="375">Nova Scotia</collectingRegion>
and in Atlantic 
<collectingCountry box="[1021,1107,659,685]" name="Canada" pageId="18" pageNumber="375">Canada</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[148,216,694,721]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="16.[140,174,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[140,1109,827,1603]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[141,1109,828,1602]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig. 5. Distribution of Colenis impunctata, Liocyrtusa luggeri, Leiodes contaminabilis, Leiodes impersonata, Leiodes neglecta, Leiodes puncticollis, Leiodes rufipes, and Leiodes triepkei in Atlantic Canada." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3770892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3770892/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="375">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). It is found mainly in woodland sites such as forest meadows, along trails and small forest roads, and in shrubbery along riverbanks (
<bibRefCitation author="Baranowski" box="[752,955,730,756]" firstAuthor="Baranowski" pageId="18" pageNumber="375" pagination="1 - 149" refId="ref22548" refString="Baranowski R (1993) Revision of the genus Leiodes Latreille of North and Central America (Coleoptera: Leiodidae). Entomological Scandinavia Supplement 42: 1 - 149." type="journal article" year="1993">Baranowski 1993</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
